  "description": [
    "Thursday July 29 1943 Page 18 Italy Can Gain Greatly By Mussolinis Firing THE forced abdication of Premier Mussolini is of great immediate advantage to the United Nation and of great ultimate advantage to Italy In assaying the military consequences of his abdica tion it is advisable to exercise restraint Italy is still in the war as the first pronouncements bv the new regime assert But the capacities of Italy for carrying on the war which were never very great are now reduced to the vanishing point It would be a wonderful thing if Italy could be induced to abandon its hopeless war without further destruction and bloodshed However it is not the instinct of even military weak nations to accept invasion and defeat on their own soil without resistance Hence the end of Mussolini is not necessarily the end of the war in Italy Nevertheless since the war has been not merely disastrous for Italy but unwanted and unpopular the hope is warranted that the end of military operations by and against Italy is near t hand THAT will be a very good thing for the United Nations because it will enable them to concentrate on the war with"
  ],
